article.description: Jibiri Blount scored a career-high 33 points and had three assists and four steals as North Carolina Central easily beat Mid-Atlantic Christian 108-63 on Monday night to win its 10th straight nonconference game at home.
article.headline: NC Central's Blount scores 33 points in 108-63 win
article.linkText: NC Central's Blount scores 33 points in 108-63 win
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. -- Jibiri Blount scored a career-high 33 points and had three assists and four steals as North Carolina Central easily beat Mid-Atlantic Christian 108-63 on Monday night to win its 10th straight nonconference game at home. Jordan Perkins made a career-high nine assists for his 372nd career helper, moving into third place on NCCU's all-time list. Evan Clayborne had 14 points and a career-high five blocks and Ty Graves added 13 points for the Eagles (4-10), who had a season-high 29 assists in hitting 45 of 76 field goals (59%). Blount was 13 of 15 from the field, Nicolas Fennell scored 12 points with six assists and Mike Melvin added 11 points. Kevin Fletcher scored 24 points and Norris Gardner added 15 for Mid-Atlantic Christian, a member of the U.S. Collegiate Athletic Association. NC Central opens Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference play on Saturday at home against Florida A&M. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
